n\nNow I'm extracting the content layers for each section. The コードサンプル shows a JSP example of the box:img tag in use. The 仕様 section contains the decision logic around resolution display modes and pixel ratio thresholds, along with an attribute reference table. The 内部構造・改修時の留意点 covers the internal implementation details, path resolution mechanics, and a component list.\n\nWriting the JSP code example...\n\nFor the 仕様 section, the component uses CSS background-image properties to switch between images based on device pixel ratio and display mode, with the same behavior in both local and server environments. It selects high-resolution images for devices with pixel ratios above 1.25:1 and low-resolution otherwise, using four distinct paths that combine the display mode (wide or compact versus narrow) with the resolution tier. Static resources need to be prepared accordingly.\n\nWhen image switching isn't necessary, files go in img/wide/high and get distributed to other directories via an img展開.bat script, with a defined priority order for file expansion and a complete attribute value reference table.\n\nFor the internal structure and maintenance considerations, CSS Media Queries handle the static file requests, path resolution follows the pattern of context path plus display mode directory plus the file attribute path, and breakpoints and image URLs depend on the template's style definitions. There are code examples for tags and templates, plus a component inventory.\n\nFor the implementation examples, I'm showing how to set up a JSP component with an id attribute that outputs an element using CSS background-image for switching images. The behavior is consistent whether running locally or on a server, and it automatically switches to high-resolution images when the device pixel ratio exceeds 1.25:1.\n\nFor the specifications section, I'm documenting the folder structure, file expansion priority rules, and the attribute table that defines all available parameters.\n\nThe internal structure uses CSS Media Queries to resolve paths based on display mode, and extensions like breakpoints or device pixel ratio changes require updates to the template configuration and tag file parameters.\n\nNow I'm assembling the full JSON structure with the index entries that organize the documentation into code samples, specifications, and implementation notes.\n\nGenerating documentation table... 高解像度画像を使うデバイスと低解像度画像を使うデバイスを分ける必要があり、画面モード(narrow/wide)と解像度(high/low)の組み合わせで4つのパスを用意する。静的ファイルの準備も含めて実装していく。\n\n基本的には`img/wide/high`に全ファイルを配置してから、バッチファイルで各ディレクトリに展開する仕組みで、展開時には既存ファイルを上書きしないようにして優先順位を管理する。\n\n次に属性値の一覧を確認していて、cssClassやidなどのウィジェット定義に必要なパラメータと、各属性がサーバ・ローカル環境でどちらが必須かを整理している。\n\nfile属性は画像の相対パスを指定する必須項目で、`img/(wide|narrow)/(high|low)/`ディレクトリ構造からの相対パスとなる。\n\nCSS Media Queryを使って静的ファイルへのリクエストを切り替え、デバイスピクセル比やブレークポイントはtemplateのstyleパラメータで管理する。デフォルトではピクセル比1.25以下を低解像度、それ以上を高解像度として扱い、IE互換性のためdppxをdpiに換算している。\n\nLooking at the component structure now...\n\nThe system uses several template files to handle different browser capabilities—one for browsers that don't support pixel ratios, another for those without media query support—along with LESS stylesheets that define the base image display and separate rules for wide and narrow image formats. There's also a JavaScript file that handles local rendering of the box_img component.\n\nNow I'm looking at the deployment structure: there's a batch script that distributes image files from the WEB-INF directory into display mode folders, with the resource images organized into subdirectories for each combination of layout type (wide or narrow) and resolution level (high or low).\n\nSince the official documentation base URL is empty, I'll set the official_doc_urls to an empty array rather than trying to populate it with a non-existent base URL.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19813,"cache_read_input_tokens":18643,"cache_creation":{"ephem